rComments: His lectures and slides are fine, but the course overall is quite disorganized... e.g. no ddl for assignments on syllabus, set the same ddl for A2 resubmission and A3 (all assignments relate to each other), inform students extended ddl on the due date, never looks at follow-ups on Piazza, handout feedbacks for A3 only one week before A4 ddl, etc.

One of my favorite profs Ive had at UofT. His tests are definitely graded hard but always fair and hes happy to explain if you dont agree. Ive learned more in his class than any other class, the only way youll benefit from this class is if you go and do the work (a very opened ended course, hard to do well but well worth it but teaches well)

Good prof, but sometimes forgets to come and teach the class (sometimes had the TA to substitute the prof). He is very caring, but does not respond to Piazza posts promptly. He also does not post lecture slides frequently. Moreover, the assignments are hard to do well in since the TAs were biased (first assignment class average was 42%).
final examination with averge 50+, won't take again
10/10 Lecturer would take again. Literally perfect.
